name: Dillon .223 Rem Carbide Rifle 3-die set
description:
The Dillon .223 Rem Carbide Rifle 3-die set is used for reloading .223 Rem or 5.56x45mm ammunition. This 3-die set includes a sizing/depriming die with full-length tungsten-carbide sizing insert, a bullet seating die and a crimp die.

All Dillon dies are hex-headed for easy adjustment using a wrench.
short_description: The Dillon .223 Rem Carbide Rifle 3-die set is used for reloading .223 Rem or 5.56x45mm ammunition. This 3-die set includes a sizing/depriming die with full-length tungsten-carbide sizing insert, a bullet seating die and a crimp die.

Sizing Die :

  • Spring-loaded floating decap assembly throws off spent primers, eliminating primer draw-back
  • Heavy-duty, headed decapping pin
  • Long, tapered carbide ring with radiussed opening is why Dillon dies work best on progressive reloaders!

Bullet seating die:

  • Quick-release die insert to clean the seating die without losing adjustment
  • Flip-flop seating stem to quickly change between RN and SWC / FP bullets
  • Vented seating stem
  • Generously radiussed die mouth for smooth progressive reloading

Crimp die :

  • Taper crimp for semi-auto pistols 
  • Accu-crimp for revolvers
  • Quick-release die insert to clean the crimp die without losing the critical crimp adjustment - especially useful when loading lead bullets!
  • Generously radiussed die mouth for smooth progressive reloading

name: Dillon .32 S&W, .32 H&R Mag Carbide Handgun 3-die set
description:
The Dillon .32 S&W, .32 H&R Mag Carbide Handgun 3-die set is used for reloading .32 S&W and/or .32 H&R Mag ammunition. This 3-die set includes a sizing/depriming die, a bullet seating die and a crimp die.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. Although all Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads, the handgun die sets do not include an expander die as this function occurs in the powder dispensing station; the calibre-specific powder funnel is part of the calibre conversion kit.

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

We recommend using Dillon case lube even on carbide pistol dies; you'll feel the significant reduction in force required to operate the machine.

name: Dillon .223 Rem Steel Rifle Crimp die
description:
The Dillon .223 Rem Steel Rifle Crimp die is used for reloading .223 Rem ammunition. The taper crimp die is specially configured to centre both the case neck and the case body, aligning the cartridge for a more uniform crimp. A taper crimp is recommended for ammunition intended to be used in semi-auto and lever-action rifles.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads.

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

name: Dillon Universal Steel Rifle Decapping die
description:
The Dillon Universal Steel Rifle Decapping die is used to prepare spent cartridge cases for reloading. This die simply removes the primer without any sizing of the cartridge case, allowing many different calibres to be prepared for subsequent case-prep actions.

Dillon dies are designed to work best on Dillon progressive reloading machines. All Dillon dies have standard 7/8"x14tpi threads.

The new 1" lock rings allow a little more space on the tool head (when adjusting  the dies) for the 1" wrench to fit.

name: Dillon RL 1050 Cartridge Bin
description:
The Dillon RL 1050 Cartridge Bin is used on the Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to catch the loaded cartridges. This bin is 260mm long, 110mm wide by 120mm deep and is great for storing just about anything.

Dillon's blue AkroBins are made of virtually unbreakable heavy-duty polypropylene. They're unaffected by weak acids and alkalis and are also water, rust and corrosion proof. They are great for reloaders requiring extra capacity, or those loading several calibers, bullet weights, bullet shapes, etc. AkroBins can be used for storing almost anything!

name: Dillon Bullet Tray Kit
description:
The Dillon Bullet Tray Kit is used to hold the bulk supply of bullets (projectiles) for reloading on the Dillon SDB, RL 550B or XL650 progressive reloading machines when these are mounted to the bench via a mounting plate. To achieve economy of motion the shallow aluminium bullet tray bolts to the left side of the machine mount at a convenient height relative to the loading platform.

This tray fits the Square Deal, RL 550 B series and XL 650 Strong Mounts from Dillon, or the equivalent machine mounts from Shooting Stuff. A mount is required in order to use this bullet tray.

name: Dillon Low Powder Sensor
description: The Dillon Low Powder Sensor is a warning system that provides an audible and visual reminder when it's time to refill your powder reservoir. A buzzer will sound and a bright LED will light when the powder level drops to about 1000 grains. The added weight of the system helps keep powder charges more consistent, especially as the level drops in the hopper. Dillon's safety sensors are for when something goes wrong and you're distracted, or not concentrating.

name: Dillon Powder Check System
description:
The Dillon Powder Check System is a valuable saftey system that checks the powder charge in each and every cartridge case during the loading process. The system detects and warns via audible beep when the charge is too high or too low.

This is a safety sensor, not an accuracy check! A powder die is included to fit the Powder Check sensor onto the tool head. The system is compatible with the XL 650 and the Super 1050 machines. Dillon's safety sensors are for when something goes wrong and you're distracted, or not concentrating.

name: Dillon Strong Mount (SDB)
description:
The Dillon Strong Mount (SDB) is a mounting system that raises the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine entirely above the bench top. Instead of stressing the leading edge the mount spreads the load over the whole bench thus contributing to a more stable setup.

If your bench is either too low for comfortable use, or you need to access drawers underneath, the strong mount elevates the entire machine above your bench top and moves it 'back', minimising anything that could be snagged in the work-area. This strong mount raises the machine by about 212mm, and is suitable for the Square Deal B machine. This kit includes a replacement spent primer cup and bracket, for older SDB machines with the plastic spent primer chute.

name: Dillon Strong Mount (RL550/XL650)
description:
The Dillon Strong Mount (RL550/XL650) is a mounting system that raises the Dillon BL550, RL550B or XL650 progressive reloading machine entirely above the bench top. Instead of stressing the leading edge the mount spreads the load over the whole bench thus contributing to a more stable setup.

If your bench is either too low for comfortable use, or you need to access drawers underneath, the strong mount elevates the entire machine above your bench top and moves it 'back', minimising anything that could be snagged in the work-area. This strong mount raises the machine by about 212mm, and is suitable for the BL550, the RL550B or the XL650 machines. This kit includes a replacement cartridge bin bracket, with ejection chute, for use on the 550-machines.

name: Dillon Toolholder with Wrench Set (SDB)
description:
The Dillon Toolholder with Wrench Set (SDB) is a bracket that mounts to the Square Deal B progressive reloading machine to organise and store a set of dipped, ball-ended Allen wrenches and the Square Deal Bench Wrench. These tools are supplied in the kit and are what's required to adjust and basically service the machine. 

The toolholder bracket mounts behind the main body of the machine, utilising the existing footprint of the machine's mounting holes and conveniently ensures that the tools are sorted and readily available when needed.

Although each Dillon progressive reloading machine is supplied with a basic set of flat-ended Allen wrenches, the ball-ended Allen wrenches included with this kit allow misaligned fitting to various bolts that makes them far more convenient to use.

name: Shooting Stuff NoSpill Primer Kit for XL650
description:
The Shooting Stuff NoSpill Primer Kit for XL650 is an upgrade to the Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine that ensures all spent primers and any unused live primers are captured and retained during the loading process. The NoSpill Primer Kit prevents any primers ending on the floor! XL 650 users are often frustrated by the ~5% of spent primers that end up on the floor, and all the more so when the occasional unused live primer follows the ski-jump to join the mess. This kit ensures that all of these primers are captured into appropriate plastic bottles; the floor remains clean and tidy!

This kit is suitable for the Dillon XL 650 machine with the "revsion B" platform, mounted on Strong Mount or Machine Mount. A plastic bottle is secured to a steel mounting bracket that affixes to the Strong Mount or Machine Mount.

name: Dillon .223 Rem Case Gauge
description:
The Dillon .223 Rem Case Gauge is a simple device that allows you to check your rifle ammunition to ensure it will fit a minimum sized chamber. Rifle headspace case gages also assist in proper sizing-die adjustment and in checking cases for whether they need to be trimmed.

The case gauge is essential for long case life, especially with semi-automatic firearms!

name: Dillon .204 Ruger Case Trim Die
description:
The Dillon .204 Ruger Case Trim Die is designed to resize and, when used together with the Dillon RT1500 or RT1200B electric case trimmers, to also trim the cartridge case to the correct length. This steel die is caliber-specific.

Brass chips / shavings are drawn off through a vaccuum manifold that clamps to the outside of the die. The vaccuum manifold is supplied seprately as part of the electric case trimmer assembly.

name: Dillon RT 1500 Electric Case Trimmer Assembly
description:
The Dillon RT 1500 Electric Case Trimmer Assembly is designed to handle the heaviest trimming jobs, including converting .223 Remi into .300 Blackout. When combined with a Dillon progressive reloading machine, especially one with an electric case feeder, the RT 1500 makes short work out of trimming large quantities of brass. Calibre-specific trim dies are sold separately.

The Dillon electic case trimmer is used just like a size die, just without the de-priming function. While you are pushing the case into the calibre-specific die to size it, a quarter- horsepower electric motor driving a carbide cutter is trimming the case to length. Brass shavings are drawn off through a vacuum manifold that clamps to the outside of the special trim die. (Vacuum cleaner and hose are not included). 

Case lube must be used. 

All the electrical & electronic components of Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty from date of purchase. This unit has a 1-year warranty.

name: Dillon RL 550B Short Trim-die Tool Head
description:
The Dillon RL 550B Short Trim-die Tool Head is required to trim short rifle cartridges like the .300 Blackout when using the RT 1500 or RT 1200B electric case trimmer on the Dillon RL 550B progressive reloading machine.

The regular tool head is too thick to achieve the correct case length with very short rifle cartridges.

This kit includes a modified vaccuum manifold.

name: Dillon CM 2000 Large Case/Media Separator
description:
The Dillon CM 2000 Large Case/Media Separator is a rotating squirrel-cage over a 18" x 22"  media collection tub, that conveniently separates the cleaned cartridge cases from the cleaning media after these have been processed in Dillon's CV 2001 vibratory case cleaner.

Simply pour the contents of the case cleaner into the open squirrel cage basket, close and latch the two halves then start turning. As you slowly rotate the basket, the cleaning media separates from the brass and falls into the media collection tub below. Just the brass remains in the basket, dry and ready to load!

name: Dillon Case Lubricant
description:
The Dillon Case Lubricant is a spray-on lanolin lubricant for reloading. Lay your cartridge cases flat in a shallow tray or box, and spray lightly with one or two passes (for handgun calibres). Shake the cases, wait a few minutes for the alcohol to evaporate and the cases are ready to load.

Dillon's Case Lube has no effect on powder or primers so it is safe to use inside cases too; this can help prevent sticking on neck expanders or powder funnels / flaring dies. We lube our cases in a beer box (Windhoek Lager) as the cardboard is absorbent, can be recycled and the box hold the right amount of cases for the Dillon XL 650 case feeder. We're OK if you prefer a different brand (of beer box)!

name: Dillon Rapid Polish 290
description:
The Dillon Rapid Polish 290 is a liquid additive to your case cleaning media that shines cases brighter than media alone and also adds a protective coating to the brass. 

Pour a few caps full over the media, let the tumbler run a few minutes to mix the polish in, then add the brass. The Rapid Polish 290 has great residual value, so less is required each time. We normally add a bit of polish every 3rd or 4th load.

name: Dillon CV 2001 Case Cleaner
description:
The Dillon CV 2001 Case Cleaner is the largest vibratory case cleaner in the industry, with a capacity for around 1 500 9mmP cases, or 550 .30-06 cases. Add a little Rapid Polish to your cleaning media and this tumbler will clean your brass shiny-bright in an hour and a half! The internally cooled, thermally protected motor is powerful enough to drive the 6kg load.

The bowl and base are both made from 5.5mm thick, injection moulded high strength polypropylene. You will require case cleaning media. We use crushed Peach Pip Media for cleaning dirty brass, and Corn Cob for a final polish! We suggest you also consider the CM 2000 Case Media Separator to conveniently separate the cases from the media. All the electrical & electronic components of Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty from date of purchase. This unit has a 1-year warranty.

name: Dillon Super Swage 600
description:
The Dillon Super Swage 600 is a simple tool to swage the primer pocket, quickly and easily. It removes the crimp typically applied to military and law enforcement brass, reforming the primer pocket to the correct size and shape. Works for large and small primers.

The Super Swage 600 supports the case from the inside, so you won't be tearing the rims off the brass. A hardened tool steel swage rod simply rolls the crimp away; no reaming is necessary. The swage rod  is easy to change from large to small primers. The Super Swage does not convert Berdan primed cases (with two small flash-holes) to Boxer (with one large flash-hole).

name: Dillon Powder Measure
description:
The Dillon Powder Measure is supplied with each Dillon progressive reloading machine. Additional powder measures are available to set up on each tool head, for your different calibres, so you never need to change your settings again. Great convenience, from Dillon!

The powder measure is infinitely adjustable (within the capacity of each powder bar) to get just the load you require. We have found great consistency, even with extruded propellant like Somchem S335. Obviously, ball and flake powders do meter more consistently than extruded powders. You will require the Dillon Extra Small Powder Bar (#20780) for charges under ~3gr, and/or the Dillon Magnum Rifle Powder Bar (#21353) for charges over ~50gr. These are available separately.

name: Dillon Powder Bar (Extra Small)
description:
The Dillon Extra Small Powder Bar is required to throw very small powder charges from your Dillon powder measure. It can throw down to ~0.5gr. It replaces the standard powder bar that comes with each Dillon powder measure.

Typical calibres requiring the extra small powder bar include .32 ACP, .32 S&W, etc. Works with all Dillon powder measures (except the Magnum system #97126)

name: Dillon Powder Die
description:
The Dillon Powder Die is used to hold the powder measure. The powder die screws into the tool head of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine and the powder measure attaches to the powder die. Additional powder dies allow you to share powder measures between calibres, while retaining the difficult -to-set flaring / belling adjustment.

The powder die is also used to hold the powder check system for the Dillon XL 650 and Super 1050 progressive reloading machines. So, sharing the sensor between tool heads becomes viable with additional powder dies.

name: Dillon Primer Flip Tray
description:
The Dillon Primer Flip Tray is a metal, two-piece device to sort primers right-side up so that they can be picked up via a primer pick-up tube for transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine.

Carefully pour the primers into the rough side of the tray and shake this gently. When all the primers are upside down (priming compound visible), place the smooth side of the tray over the rough side, sandwiching the primers inside. While keeping the two parts squeezed gently, yet firmly, together, flip the tray over. Remove the rough side, leaving the primers on the smooth side of the tray, each one shiny-side up. The primers are now ready to be picked up by dabbing each with the tip of an appropraite primer pick-up tube.
short_description: The Dillon Primer Flip Tray is a metal, two-piece device to sort primers right-side up so that they can be picked up via a primer pick-up tube for transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine.

name: Dillon Magnum Powder Measure
description:
The Dillon Magnum Powder Measure is capable of dispensing over 100gr of extruded propellant, so is just what you need when loading lots of ammo for big, powerful calibres like .338 Lapua Magnum, .416 Rigby, .458 Lott, etc.

The powder measure is infinitely adjustable (within the capacity of each powder bar) to get just the load you require, and is supplied with the oversize powder die (#21253) needed for calibres too large in diameter to fit in the standard powder die (#20064). We have found great consistency, even with extruded propellant like Somchem S335. Obviously, ball and flake powders do meter more consistently than extruded powders. In testing with a range of extruded rifle powders, Dillon found that the charge variation was ±0.3gr.

name: Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler (Large, 220V)
description:
The Dillon RF 100 Automatic Primer Filler (Large, 220V) is an electrically powered machine to sort and transfer a hundred large primers from their packaging box into a "tansfer tube", for subsequent transfer into the primer magazine of your favourite Dillon progressive reloading machine.

The RF 100 eliminates the need to manually fill primer pick-up tubes. Carefully pour the primers from their box into the top of the RF 100, press the blue button and watch it run! Yes, it's fun to watch but you could also load about 30 rounds while the RF 100 does its work. Within two minutes the RF 100 sorts the primers right way up and fills the "tramsfer tube" with a hundred primers; a timer shuts the machine off after about 2 minutes. All the electrical & electronic components of Dillon equipment are covered by a one-year warranty from date of purchase.ÊThis unit has a 1-year warranty.

name: Dillon SDB DVD Instruction Manual
description:
The Dillon SDB DVD Instruction Manual is an electronic user guide with expert step-by-step instructions for unpacking, assembling, setting up and safely operating your Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine.

This Hybrid DVD features close-up views and reloader's view perspective to cover loading a pistol round. Changing calibers and the use of optional equipment is also featured.Bonus content, accessed via your PC with DVD-drive, includes a printable reloader's log book, handy web-links.

name: DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos
description:
The DVD: Competition Reloading with Brian Enos is a step-by-step guide through the reloading process for IPSC, Steel Challenge and other action-shooting styles of shooting. Brian uses the Dillon XL 650 to demonstrate the proper reloading techniques used by top shooters to develop the right loads.

Brian Enos is a champion himself. Winner of the Master Competition and the NRA Bianchi Cup, Brian also competed in IPSC and USPSA for many years.

name: Dillon 38/357 Super 1050 Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon 38/357 Super 1050 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .38 Spl and/or .357 Mag calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

If you don't already have it, you may require the small pistol case feeder plate (#21073), available seprately. The case feed spacer washer (#13703, supplied with the original case feeder assembly) should be installed for this calibre. You may also require the small primer system for this calibre (#20419).
short_description: The Dillon 38/357 Super 1050 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .38 Spl and/or .357 Mag calibre ammunition. name: Dillon 7.62x39mm Super 1050 Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon 7.62x39mm Super 1050 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon Super 1050 progressive reloading machine to be able to load 7.62x39mm calibre (AK-47) ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

If you don't already have it, you may require the large rifle case feeder plate (#21075), available seprately. You may also require either the large primer system for this calibre (#20476), or the small primer system for this calibre (#20419). The 7.62x39mm calibre generally uses large primers, but Remington-made brass uses small primers.

name: Dillon Super 1050 Quick Change Kit
description:
The Dillon Super 1050 Quick Change Kit is a cost-saving packaging of the Super 1050 tool head and powder measure. The Quick-Change makes it easy to change calibres by completely setting up dies, powder measure and optional powder check system (#21044) in a tool head for each calibre.

The tool head holds the dies in perfect alignment so no re-adjustment is necessary when changing between calibres.

name: Dillon .22 Hornet RL 550B Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon .22 Hornet RL 550B Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon RL 550B progressive reloading machine to be able to load .22 Hornet and similar calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

Shooting Stuff prices and supplies the calibre conversion kit separately for the RL 550B, so it is required for the first and any subsequent calibres. This is just the way Dillon supplies the system to us! This kit comprises the 4-station shell plate, three brass locator buttons and powder funnel, the silver, cylindrical insert that goes in the powder die.

description:
The Dillon RL 550B Quick Change Kit is a cost-saving packaging of the RL 550B tool head, powder measure and cast tool head stand. The Quick-Change kit makes it easy to change calibres by completely setting up dies and powder measure in a tool head for each calibre.

name: Dillon RL 550B Case Feeder
description:
The Dillon RL 550B Case Feeder is an upgrade to the Dillon RL 550B progressive reloading machine to automatically feed handgun-calibre cartridge cases into the machine, adding convenience and increasing loading rate. Requires the additional purchase of a caliber specific conversion kit, and a suitable case feeder plate.

This case feeder is similar to the one used on Dillon's commercial-grade Super 1050 machine and the XL 650. Lube your cases then simply dump them into the hopper and turn it on. The 220V electric motor-driven disc fills the case feed tube and a mechanical system feeds the cases into the shell plate. A micro-switch shuts off the motor when the tube is full, and automatically restarts it when low. The case feeder can be used for large pistol calibres by purchasing a large pistol case feeder plate (#21072), and/or for small pistol calibres by purchasing a small pistol case feeder plate (#21073).

name: CED Universal Digital Pocket Scale
description:
The CED Universal Digital Pocket Scale is a compact, inexpensive electronic scale, one of the best we've found in this category. It has a massive 3 000 grain capacity!

Like all inexpensive electronic scales this one is also prone to unpredictable zero-drift, so requires careful use and frequent re-zeroing. Use casefully and with understanding. This scale is not suitable for powder trickling! If you desire hassle-free use we rather recommend the Dillon D-Terminator electronic scale (#10483).

name: Shooting Stuff RL 550B Quick Mount Kit
description:
The Shooting Stuff RL 550B Quick Mount Kit is a cost-saving packaging of their Machine Mount and Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket for the Dillon RL550 progressive reloading machine, together with Dillon's Cast Bullet Tray kit.

If your bench is either too low for comfortable use, or you need to access drawers underneath, the Machine Mount elevates the entire machine above your bench top and moves it "back", minimising anything that could be snagged in the work-area.

This kit includes a Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket, with ejection chute, for use on the 550-machines, that also positions the empty cardridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon RL550B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1.

The Dillon Bullet Tray Kit is used to hold the bulk supply of bullets (projectiles) for reloading on the left side of the Dillon RL 550B progressive reloading machine.

name: Dillon Eliminator Balance Beam Scale
description:
The Dillon Eliminator Balance Beam Scale is a magnetically damped, mechanical scale designed for reloading, with a 500 grain capacity accurate to ±0.1 grain.

Balance-beam scales are reliable and dependable, with no electronics to drift and no batteries to change.

This dependability has only one drawback, they are slower to use than electronic scales for unknown masses. That said, they are ideal for trickling in powder charges to a known weight.

name: Somchem reloading manual, 2nd edition
description:
The Somchem reloading manual, 2nd edition is the definitive loading data source for the locally manufactured propellants from RDM-Somchem. The manual incudes information on the fundamental facts and principles of internal ballistics and firearm kinetics.

This manual also offers a chart showing the comparative burn rates and relative positioning of propellants from the major propellant manufacturers.

description:
The Rudy Project Rydon Shooters Pack is a set of Rydon shooting glasses supplied with five lenses for varying conditions. The Rydon is the most comfortable glasses we have found for shooting with hearing protection. This set has Matte Black frames and five different fixed-tint, polycarbonte lenses; Racing Red, Laser Copper, Transparent, Yellow, Action Brown.

Rudy Project RO Optics lenses offer industry standard eye protection (mechanical and chemical) with guaranteed visual acuity. These lightweight lenses ensure wearer comfort and reduce glare while enhacing contrast to ensure "true vision" without distortion of colours.Ultraviolet radiation is completely neutralised up to 400 nm (UV 400 Protection). The Quick Change Interchangeable Lens System allows easy upgrade to include any Rydon lenses, including ImpactX 2, or prescription ImpaxtRx 2 technology.

name: Frontier CMJ Bullets - 9mmP 124gr RN, .355" (sample of 100)
description:
The Frontier CMJ Bullets - 9mmP 124gr RN, .355" (sample of 100) is a pack of premium handgun bullets ideal for reloading 9mm calibres. This sample pack of 100 makes it affordable to test different loads before spending a lot on bullets.

CMJ Bullets are known for their accuracy, consistency and superb performance. These bullets have been restriked, this process forces the finished bullet into a shaping die to remove any imperfections and to ensure that the bullet fits its designed shape perfectly.

name: Dillon .38 / .357 SDB Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon .38 / .357 SDB Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine to be able to load .38 / .357 and similar calibre ammunition. The unique SDB dies form part of this kit.

Although the Square Deal B uses tungsten carbide sizing dies, we strongly recommend using case lube. Dillon's spray-on liube is easy to apply!
short_description: The Dillon .38 / .357 SDB Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine to be able to load .38 / .357 and similar calibre ammunition. The unique SDB dies form part of this kit.

name: Shooting Stuff SDB Quick Mount Kit
description:
The Shooting Stuff SDB Quick Mount Kit is a cost-saving packaging of their Machine Mount and Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket  for the Dillon SDB progressive reloading machine, together with Dillon's Cast Bullet Tray kit.

If your bench is either too low for comfortable use, or you need to access drawers underneath, the Machine Mount elevates the entire machine above your bench top and moves it "back", minimising anything that could be snagged in the work-area.

This kit includes a Cartridge Case Bin & Bracket, with ejection chute, that also positions the empty cartridge cases conveniently on the right-hand side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine, ready for inserting into station 1.

The Dillon Bullet Tray Kit is used to hold the bulk supply of bullets (projectiles) for reloading on the left side of the Dillon Square Deal B progressive reloading machine.

name: Dillon Large Pistol Casefeed Plate
description:
The Dillon Large Pistol Casefeed Plate is the grey disc for the Dillon electric casefeeder that sorts the large pistol cases, like .45 ACP. It is an essential component of the casefeed assembly for this specific range of cartridge cases.

There are only five casefeed plates to cover all calibres: * Small pistol for handgun calibres like 9mm, .38 Spl, etc. *Small rifle for rifle calibres like .223 Rem, etc. * Large pistol for handgun calibres like .45 ACP, .44 mag, etc. * Large rifle for rifle calibres like .308 Win, .30-06, etc. * Magnum rifle for belted magnum rifle calibres, like .375 H&H, etc. Please refer to the XL650 manual (available here) for guidance on the correct plate for each calibre.

name: Brian Enos: Practical Shooting Beyond Fundamentals
description:
The Brian Enos: Practical Shooting Beyond Fundamentals is a nine-chapter paperback book that talks about the keys to consistent, high-speed shooting and includes a comprehensive set of exercises to help you to incorporate this into your shooting game.

This 201 page book includes the following chapters: Awareness & Focus, Tools of Shooting, Creative Shooting, Specific Challenges, Competition, Development, Shooting Tools, Revolver Shooting & Group Shooting.

name: Brian Enos's Far Superior Slide Glide - Lite (15ml tube)
description:
The Brian Enos's Far Superior Slide Glide - Lite is an expertly formulated lubricant that protects firearms from wear and corrosion and softens felt recoil in semi-automatic firearms, particularly pistols.

Slide-Glide is formulated to have a stringy consistency that prevents spreading and tracking on sliding metal surfaces. It stays put in the friction areas of the cycling slide and barrel, providing a dramatic improvement in lubrication compared to conventional oils and greases.

name: CED M2 Chronograph
description:
The CED M2 Chronograph is an update to the CED Millennium Chronograph which has been an industry standard for the past eight years! The M2 has double the operating speed of its predecessor, incorporating a micro-controller that runs at 48 MHz, it expands the operation range from 50 fps to 7,000 fps. The storage capacity of this model has also been expanded, enabling storage of over 1000 stored velocities!

With the expanded digital chip design, the M2 can read velocities at much lower light levels, from early morning till almost sunset! In addition to all the improvements, the M2 also has a USB interface, making it easier than ever to download and save your data to your PC using the CED Data Collector Software.

name: CED 7000 Shot Activated Timer
description:
The CED 7000 Shot Activated Timer is a compact, easy to operate, full featured timer. The timer features custom PAR for single or multiple time settings, variable delay intervals to .01 seconds, an easy-to-read illuminated display countdown mode and auxiliary jack for external loud horn, visual starts or target turning! 

The timer has a 999.99 second time record capacity and can be upgraded for wireless connection to a CED BigBoard or Time Keeper for displaying results more than 40 meters away from the timer.

The CED 8000 Shot Timer is a state-of-the-art electronic timer designed to drastically improve your shooting game! This shot-activated timer provides all timing functions any competitive shooter needs in one portable, easy-to-use, dependable package. 

This shot timer features an easy-to-read illuminated LCD display, unlimited shot record and review, 999.99 sec time record capacity, split time recording, programmed NRA Bianchi, PPC and Field Shooting events, Sportsman Challenge Countdown and Gunsmith Modes and much more!

name: CED BigBoard Display
description:
The CED BigBoard Display is an LCD display board that provides a synchronised connection to a host linked shot timer. This board enables you to see actual time as it is recorded by either the CED 7000 RF or CED 8000 RF shot timers from up to 45 meters away!

The BigBoard comes with a wall mounting option as well as removable table stands for flexible display options. The protective carry case included makes it easy to take it with you wherever you go.

name: CED 8000 RF Shot Timer with Big Board
description:
CED 8000 RF Shot Timer with Big Board is a combo deal featuring the CED 8000 RF, a state-of-the-art shot activated electronic timer and the CED BigBoard Display with a large LCD 4-segment screen. A wireless synchronised connection between these two products will enable you to view actual time as it is recorded from up to 45 meters away!

The CED 8000 Shot Timer is a state-of-the-art electronic timer provides all timing functions any competitive shooter needs in one portable, easy-to-use, dependable package. This shot timer features an easy-to-read illuminated LCD display, unlimited shot record and review, 999.99 sec time record capacity, split time recording, programmed NRA Bianchi, PPC and Field Shooting events, Sportsman Challenge Countdown and Gunsmith Modes and much more!

The CED BigBoard Display connects wirelessly to your shot timer to enable you to see actual time as it is recorded by either the CED 7000 RF or CED 8000 RF shot timers from up to 45 meters away! The BigBoard comes with a wall mounting option as well as removable table stands for flexible display options. The protective carry case included makes it easy to take it with you wherever you go.

name: Wilson 1911 Elite Tactical Magazine - 9mm [10 round]
description:
The Wilson 1911 Elite Tactical Magazine - 9mm is a full size, 10 round magazine with an ETM base pad. The tube is made from aircraft-grade certified stainless steel that resists corrosion and increases reliability in your pistol!

The radius of curves on this magazine body are engineered to minimise stress points, eliminating feed lip cracking and stress fatigue. The position of the witness slots are moved towards the rear to further enhance this structural integrity.

The state-of-the-art materials and manufacturing technology, makes this ultra-reliable magazine perfect for competition, combat or self-defense!
short_description: The Wilson 1911 Elite Tactical Magazine - 9mm is a full size, 10 round magazine with an ETM base pad. The tube is made from aircraft-grade certified stainless steel that resists corrosion and increases reliability in your pistol!

name: UniqueTek Micrometer Powder Bar Kit
description:
Much like Shooting Stuff, UniqueTek was founded out of the frustration over finding specialty products for reloading and other accessories for sport shooting. UniqueTek has developed many of these products and distributes many other really useful, hard-to-find items. Shooting Stuff is proud to represent UniqueTek in South Africa and holds stock of most of the popular products.

name: Sierra 20 Cal / .204" 39gr BlitzKing
description:
The Sierra 20 / .204 39gr BlitzKing is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 20 (.204) calibres.

Blitzking bullets have an accuracy characteristic of the Matchking bullets, and are designed for explosive expansion in small game and varmints. The sharp acetyl resin compound nose tips improve the ballistic coefficient over the traditional flat-base spritzer design.

This bullet features a thin jacket to further enhance the explosive expansion and accuracy while still being capable of withstanding high velocities.

name: Sierra 22 Cal / .224" 45gr RN Varminter
description:
The Sierra 22 / .224 45gr RN Varminter is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

This Varminter bullet features a thin-walled jacket, a soft core and a traditional round nose shape. It is suitable for 22 Hornet, 22 K-Hornet, or 218 Bee or similar cartridges with muzzle velocities ranging 2600 to 2900 fps. At these modest velocities, this thin-jacket round-nose bullet provides outstanding accuracy and effective expansion on small varmints.

It is also effective in rifles firing medium-capacity cartridges, such as the 222 Remington and 223 Remington, for target and varmint shooting at muzzle velocities up to 3500 fps.

name: Sierra 22 Cal / .224" 55gr Blitz Varminter
description:
The Sierra 22 / .224 55gr Blitz Varminter is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

This Varminter bullet is the ideal bullet for the popular 222 Remington and 223 Remington as it is designed for maximum terminal performance at velocity levels typical to these rifles. The accuracy achieved by this bullet is comparable to the Matchking bullets.

This bullet features a sleek Spitzer shape point enhanced downrange performance. This light jacket bullet should only be used in conventional twist-rate barrels (1x12 inch / 1x14 inch) as fast rate bullets can cause the bullet to disintegrate in mid air.

name: Sierra 22 Cal / .224" 55gr SPT Varminter
description:
The Sierra 22 / .224 55gr SPT Varminter is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

This Varminter bullet is fully capable of yielding _ minute of angle accuracy at velocities that would destroy most other bullets. This bullet features a Spitzer point shape and a flat base with a precisely drawn jacket resulting in pinpoint accuracy and reliable expansion, even at maximum ranges.

This bullet is especially well suited for velocities ranging from 22-250 and 220 Swift cartridges.

name: Sierra 22 Cal / .224" 55gr SBT GameKing
description:
The Sierra 22 / .224 55gr SBT GameKing is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

Gameking bullets are designed for dependable expansion and deep penetration in medium and heavy game animals.

This bullet has a Spitzer Boat Tail (SBT) shape that significantly reduces the base drag, resulting in a higher ballistic coefficient compared to flat base bullets of the same weight.

Boat tail bullets are less sensitive to crosswinds, with a higher retained velocity downrange, flatter trajectory, and higher energy delivered to the target when compared to their flat base equivalents.

name: Sierra 22 Cal / .224" 63gr SMP (semi-pointed)
description:
The Sierra 22 / .224 63gr SMP (semi-pointed) is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

This Semi-Point bullet was designed to expand faster than the Spitzer due to a great amount of exposed lead at the tip and the slightly larger opening in the jacket. The Semi-Point design reduces the bullet’s length for its weight, resulting in a more stable bullet, although, it does have a lower ballistic coefficient than its Spitzer pointed equivalent.

This bullet is suitable for use in early 22 centerfire rifles and in modern rifles with faster twist rates.

The Sierra 22 / .224 60gr HP Varminter is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 22 (.224) calibres.

This high-velocity bullet is designed for precision accuracy with the explosive expansion of Sierra's Varminter-style construction. This bullet is best suited for larger-capacity cartridges such as 22-250 or 220 Swift with 1x14 inch twist rate barrels.

This bullet has a very thin jacket drawn to an exacting concentricity standard of 0.0003 in maximum variation, its weight held to within ± 0.3 grain.

This bullet has a hollow point (HP) design with a very small meplat resulting in a high ballistic coefficient. The boat tail design on this bullet further improves the ballistic coefficient and reduces base drag.

Matchking bullets are not recommended for most hunting applications.

name: Sierra 30 Cal / .308" 150gr FN Pro-Hunter
description:
The Sierra 30 / .308 150gr FN Pro-Hunter is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 30 (.308) calibres.

This Pro-hunter bullet was designed specifically for 30-30 Win cartridges, featuring a jacket tailored to 30-30 velocities. However, the use of this bullet is not restricted to30-30, it is very effective in any 30 caliber cartridge with a maximum muzzle velocity level of 2600 fps.

This bulletÕs cannelure is precisely located for proper over all length, resulting in fast, trouble-free feeding. The power jacket construction on this bullet ensures reliable expansion and good penetration, making it a suitable option for deer-sized game.

name: Sierra 30 Cal / .308" 180gr SBT GameKing
description:
The Sierra 30 / .308 180gr SBT GameKing is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 30 (.308) calibres.

Gameking bullets are designed for dependable expansion and deep penetration in medium and heavy game animals.

This bullet has a Spitzer Boat Tail (SBT) shape that significantly reduces the base drag, resulting in a higher ballistic coefficient compared to flat base bullets of the same weight.

Boat tail bullets are less sensitive to crosswinds, with a higher retained velocity downrange, flatter trajectory, and higher energy delivered to the target when compared to their flat base equivalents.

name: Sierra 30 Cal / .308" 168gr HPBT MatchKing
description:
The Sierra 30 / .308 168gr HPBT MatchKing is a box of 100 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 30 (.308) calibres.

The Matchking is Sierra’s pre-eminent target bullet, having been used to win more target competitions than all target bullets from other manufacturers combined! The main driving force behind the design of this bullet is its accuracy that has been acclaimed worldwide. This bullet has a very thin jacket drawn to an exacting concentricity standard of 0.0003 in maximum variation, its weight held to within ± 0.3 grain.

This bullet has a hollow point (HP) design with a very small meplat resulting in a high ballistic coefficient. The boat tail design on this bullet further improves the ballistic coefficient and reduces base drag.

Matchking bullets are not recommended for most hunting applications.

The Matchking is Sierra’s pre-eminent target bullet, having been used to win more target competitions than all target bullets from other manufacturers combined! The main driving force behind the design of this bullet is its accuracy that has been acclaimed worldwide. This bullet has a very thin jacket drawn to an exacting concentricity standard of 0.0003 in maximum variation, its weight held to within ± 0.3 grain.

This bullet has a hollow point (HP) design with a very small meplat resulting in a high ballistic coefficient. The boat tail design on this bullet further improves the ballistic coefficient and reduces base drag.

Matchking bullets are not recommended for most hunting applications.

name: Sierra 375 Cal / .375" 300gr SBT GameKing (50 p/b)
description:
The Sierra 375 / .375 300gr SBT GameKing is a box of 50 rifle bullets, ideal for reloading 375 (.375) calibres.

Gameking bullets are designed for dependable expansion and deep penetration in medium and heavy game animals.

This bullet has a Spitzer Boat Tail (SBT) shape that significantly reduces the base drag, resulting in a higher ballistic coefficient compared to flat base bullets of the same weight.

Boat tail bullets are less sensitive to crosswinds, with a higher retained velocity downrange, flatter trajectory, and higher energy delivered to the target when compared to their flat base equivalents.

name: Dillon XL 650 / Super 1050  Case Feeder (No Plate)
description:
The Dillon XL 650 / Super 1050 Case Feeder is a 220V electrically powered device to automatically sort cartridge cases "the right way up" and systematically feed them into the Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine's vertical casefeed tube. Just dump a bunch of brass into the blue hopper, turn it on and the casefeeder automatically orients the brass mouth-up and fills the casefeed tube.

The Dillon Casefeeder is a popular optional accessory for the Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine and is included as standard equipment with the commercial-grade Super 1050. It is often used to supply cartridge cases to other devices too! You must also order a suitable casefeed plate for the required calibre(s). There are only five plates to cover all calibres:

  • Small pistol for handgun calibres like 9mm, .38 Spl, etc.
  • Small rifle for rifle calibres like .223 Rem, etc.
  • Large pistol for handgun calibres like .45 ACP, .44 mag, etc.
  • Large rifle for rifle calibres like .308 Win, .30-06, etc.
  • Magnum rifle for belted magnum rifle calibres, like .375 H&H, etc.

Please refer to the XL650 manual (available here) for guidance on the correct plate for each calibre.

The Dillon XL 650 Spare Parts Kit is an assortment of the small bits that easily get lost, or could wear-out or break.

Murphy's Law says that if something could go wrong, it will and at the worst possible moment. This kit keeps you going until Shooting Stuff and Dillon replace these parts, at no charge if they are under warranty.

name: Dillon Super 1050 Toolhead Stand (blue)
description:
The Dillon Super 1050 Toolhead Stand (blue) is used to hold a spare tool head upright on the shelf, eliminating clutter from the reloading bench. It is made for the Dillon Super 1050 or RL 1050.

The stand holds the die-filled tool head, with or without a powder measure fitted.

name: Dillon .300 Win Mag XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon .300 Win Mag XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .300 Win Mag and similar calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

This kit comprises the 5-station shell plate, three brass locator buttons and powder funnel, the silver, cylindrical insert that goes in the powder die. It also includes the small case feed parts from the bottom of the case feed tube to the shell plate.
short_description: The Dillon .300 Win Mag XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .300 Win Mag and similar calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

description:
The Dillon .30-30 Winchester XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .30-30 Winchester and similar calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

This kit comprises the 5-station shell plate, three brass locator buttons and powder funnel, the silver, cylindrical insert that goes in the powder die. It also includes the small case feed parts from the bottom of the case feed tube to the shell plate.

Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

name: Dillon .38 SuperComp XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit
description:
The Dillon .38 SuperComp XL 650 Caliber Conversion Kit is a box of the calibre-specific items required to convert your Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine to be able to load .38 SuperComp and similar calibre ammunition. Dies are not part of this kit, and should be procured separately.

This kit comprises the 5-station shell plate, three brass locator buttons and powder funnel, the silver, cylindrical insert that goes in the powder die. It also includes the small case feed parts from the bottom of the case feed tube to the shell plate.

name: Shooting Stuff XL 650 Quick Mount Kit
description:
The Shooting Stuff XL 650 Quick Mount Kit is a cost-saving packaging of their Machine Mount and NoSpill Primer Kit for the Dillon XL 550 progressive reloading machine, together with Dillon's Cast Bullet Tray kit.

If your bench is either too low for comfortable use, or you need to access drawers underneath, the Machine Mount elevates the entire machine above your bench top and moves it "back", minimising anything that could be snagged in the work-area. This kit includes an upgrade kit to reliably capture spent and unused live primers, preventing them ending on the floor. The Dillon Bullet Tray Kit is used to hold the bulk supply of bullets (projectiles) for reloading on the left side of the Dillon XL 650 progressive reloading machine.

name: Frontier CMJ Bullets - 223 Rem 55gr SP, .223" (sample of 100)
description:
The Frontier CMJ Bullets - 223 Rem 55gr SP, .223" (sample of 100) is a pack of premium bullets ideal for reloading 223 calibres. This sample pack of 100 makes it affordable to test different loads before spending a lot on bullets.

CMJ Bullets are known for their accuracy, consistency and superb performance. These bullets have been restriked, this process forces the finished bullet into a shaping die to remove any imperfections and to ensure that the bullet fits its designed shape perfectly.

name: CED 7000 Tactical Shot Timer
description:
The CED 7000 Tactical Shot Timer is a sleek, all-black version of the CED7000 shot timer. This compact, easy to operate, full featured timer features custom PAR for single or multiple time settings, variable delay intervals to .01 seconds, an easy-to-read illuminated display countdown mode and auxiliary jack for external loud horn, visual starts or target turning! 

The timer has a 999.99 second time record capacity and can be upgraded for wireless connection to a CED BigBoard or Time Keeper for displaying results more than 40 meters away from the timer.

name: Dillon XL 650 Quick Change Kit
description:
The Dillon XL 650 Quick Change Kit is a cost-saving packaging of the XL 650 tool head, powder measure and cast tool head stand. The Quick-Change kit makes it easy to change calibres by completely setting up dies and powder measure in a tool head for each calibre.

The tool head holds the dies in perfect alignment so no re-adjustment is necessary when changing between calibres.

name: Once-Fired Cartridge Cases - .25 ACP / 6.35mm (100)
description:
The Once-Fired Cartridge Cases - .25 ACP / 6.35mm is a pack of (100) cartridge cases sourced from single-use ranges. In this way we are able to ensure that this brass is genuinely once-fired. The cases are all cleaned and sorted into lots with the same head stamp (where quantities allow). Where necessary the cases are de-primed and the primer pocket swaged to remove any crimp.

Shooting Stuff's Once-fired Cartridge Cases are guarranteed to be once-fired, are all Boxer-primed and are also sorted into batches of the same brand so that you can reload the best possible ammunition! The Good Used Cartridge Cases - .38 Spl is a pack of (100) cartridge cases sourced from commercial ranges. While most are likely once-fired, we are not able to ensure this. The cases are all cleaned and, where necessary, de-primed and the primer pocket swaged to remove any crimp.

This good used brass is supplied in mixed lots, i.e. unsorted. Nevertheless, we do try to ensure that all cases are reloadable, i.e. Boxer-primed.

Do you need greater consistency? Shooting Stuff's Once-fired Cartridge Cases are guarranteed to be once-fired, are all Boxer-primed and are also sorted into batches of the same brand.

name: Good Used Cartridge Cases - .30-30 Win (50)
description:
The Good Used Cartridge Cases - .30-30 Win is a pack of (50) cartridge cases sourced from commercial ranges. While most are likely once-fired, we are not able to ensure this. The cases are all cleaned and, where necessary, de-primed and the primer pocket swaged to remove any crimp.

This good used brass is supplied in mixed lots, i.e. unsorted. Nevertheless, we do try to ensure that all cases are reloadable, i.e. Boxer-primed.

name: CCI 200 Large Rifle Primers #0011 (1000)
description:
The CCI 200 Large Rifle Primers is a pack of 1000 percussion caps used to reload standard large rifle cartridges.

Once struck by the firing pin the primer ignites the main powder charge, firing the bullet! The primer is found at the base of the cartridge case and is a replaceable part of the cartridge during reloading. CCI Primers utilise non-corrosive and non-mercuric initiator mixes selected for their clean burning characteristics.

All CCI Primers have a larger anvil area to compensate for firearms that may have an off-centre firing pin and are engineered to enable smooth feeding in automated reloading equipment.

Once struck by the firing pin the primer ignites the main powder charge, firing the bullet! The primer is found at the base of the cartridge case and is a replaceable part of the cartridge during reloading. name: CCI 250 Large Rifle Magnum Primers #0015 (1000)
description:
The CCI 250 Large Rifle Magnum Primers is a pack of 1000 percussion caps used to reload large rifle cartridges requiring magnum loads.

Once struck by the firing pin the primer ignites the main powder charge, firing the bullet! The primer is found at the base of the cartridge case and is a replaceable part of the cartridge during reloading. CCI Primers utilise non-corrosive and non-mercuric initiator mixes selected for their clean burning characteristics.

All CCI Primers have a larger anvil area to compensate for firearms that may have an off-centre firing pin and are engineered to enable smooth feeding in automated reloading equipment.

Large cases, cold weather, and certain propellants often require a hotter primer flame and a longer burn than that provided by a standard primer. The CCI 250 Large Rifle Magnum Primers offer an increase of ~23% hotter flame over standard, with an increased flame duration.

categories: root/Guns and Ammo,root/Guns and Ammo/Handguns/Pistols,root/Guns and Ammo/Handguns/Pistols/Glock
name: Glock G17 Gen 3 9x19 Standard Pistol
description:
The Glock G17 Gen 3 9x19 Standard Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This third generation handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.

  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.

  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

Standard models are well suited to open carry by law enforcement officers, and remain popular with competition shooters and larger framed people for concealed carry.

name: Glock G17 Gen 4 SILC 9x19 Standard Pistol
description:
The Glock G17 Gen 4 SILC 9x19 Standard Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 17 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available. The SILC-models have an extended barrel, threaded for an accessory such as a silencer, or compensator.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.

  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.

  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

Standard models are well suited to open carry by law enforcement officers, and remain popular with competition shooters and larger framed people for concealed carry.

name: Glock G22 Gen 4 .40 S&W Standard Pistol
description:
The Glock G22 Gen 4 .40 S&W Standard Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 40 S&W calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.

  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.

  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

Standard models are well suited to open carry by law enforcement officers, and remain popular with competition shooters and larger framed people for concealed carry.

name: Glock G33 .357 SIG Sub-Compact Pistol
description:
The Glock G33 .357 SIG Sub-Compact Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 357 SIG calibre ammunition. This third generation handgun holds 9 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.

  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.

  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

categories: root/Guns and Ammo,root/Guns and Ammo/Handguns/Pistols,root/Guns and Ammo/Handguns/Pistols/Glock
name: Glock G35 Gen 4 MOS .40 S&W Competition Pistol
description:
The Glock G35 Gen 4 MOS .40 S&W Competition Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 40 S&W calibre ammunition. This fourth generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available. This model is designed specifically to comply with IPSC Standard Gun size limitations. The MOS-models are designed to accept ruggedised Miniature Optical Sights, mounted to the slide.

Glock Safe-Action pistols were introduced in the 1980's and have excelled in military, police and civilian environments. The Glock was the first commercially successful polymer framed handgun. Initially offered in 9x19mm Glock pistols are now available in many other calibres too.

With several different sizes available, there is a Glock to suit almost any requirement. Long-slide models are great for competition, standard models are well suited for officers on duty, for example, and the compact, sub-compact or slimline models offer a balanced, self-defence capability. Their versatility ensures that most models are multi-functional, serving well for home defence, daily carry, duty or competition!

The polymer frame and grip is tough, lightweight and corrosion resistant. Tenifer, the 'nearly hard as diamond' Glock surface treatment, protects the barrel and slide while remaining anti-reflective.

Shooting Stuff recommends Glock pistols! With minimal external controls they are extremely easy to use and to learn to use, for left-handed and right-handed shooters! They are reliable, durable and lightweight. Three independent, automatic safety features ensure that the pistol fires when, and only when, the trigger is deliberately pulled. All three safety features re-engage when the trigger is released, automatically securing the pistol again. We believe that Glock is the best supported firearms brand in South Africa, with spares, magazines, holsters and many aftermarket accessories available ex-stock.

Three automatic safety features:

  1. The trigger safety prevents inadvertent firing by lateral force on the trigger, and is automatically depressed when initial tension is applied to the trigger. It automatically resets when the trigger is released.

  2. The firing pin safety is a hardened steel plunger that blocks the firing pin from igniting the chambered cartridge until the trigger is pulled to the rear, pushing the firing pin safety up and out of the way. It automatically reactivates when the trigger is released.

  3. The drop safety prevents the trigger mechanism from "activating" and firing an unintentional shot in the event that the pistol drops or falls onto a hard surface. Only with sufficient rearward travel of the trigger can the firing pin be released, firing the shot.

The extractor serves as a loaded chamber indicator, and the trigger offers further visual and tactile cues to the gun's status.

The extended barrel length and longer sight radius of the competition models offer greater precision to competitive shooters and special units.

The CZ 75 B Omega 9x19 Standard Pistol is a proven firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 16 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The timeless CZ 75 is the mainstay from the Czech firearms company, and modern variants now include the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch and an automatic firing pin block.

The top of the slide is enhanced with an anti-reflection coating for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots.

This model has a manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch, not the decocker.

name: CZ P-01 9x19 Compact Pistol
description:
The CZ P-01 9x19 Compact Pistol is a modern evolution of the proven CZ 75 pistol, with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 14 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

SP-01, the modern range of handguns from the Czech firearms company, includes the baby of that family, the P-01. This pistol is designed for concealed carry, yet features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism (from 2016 production).

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch / decocker (from 2016 production) and an automatic firing pin block.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots. Self-illuminating, Tritium night sights are an available option.

The currently available model (pre-2016) has a manually operated, frame-mounted decocker without the Omega trigger.

name: CZ P-07 Duty 9x19 Compact Pistol
description:
The CZ P-07 Duty 9x19 Compact Pistol is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This first generation handgun holds 15 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

The CZ P-07 is one of a modern range of polymer-framed handguns from the Czech firearms company. This pistol is designed for concealed carry as well as law-enforcement, yet features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch (optionally a decocker) and an automatic firing pin block. All these are built around the proven Omega trigger system.

The slide features front serrations for easy cocking and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots. Self-illuminating, Tritium night sights are an available option. Steel parts have an extremely durable surface finish.

The durable, fibreglass-reinforced polymer frame features an integral accessory rail for weapon-mounted lights, etc. The grip offers interchangeable backstraps that allows the shooter to alter the ergonomics to their preferred grip size - small, medium or large. The magazine release catch is reversible for left-handed shooters.

This first generation model does not feature all of these innovations: No front serrations on the slide. Only the standard safety catch is included. The grip size cannot be altered. Only standard capacity basepads are included for the magazines.

name: CZ P-09 9x19 Standard Pistol (FDE)
description:
The CZ P-09 9x19 Standard Pistol (FDE) is a modern firearm with a lightweight polymer frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This first generation handgun holds 19 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity and/or extended capacity magazines are available.

The CZ P-09 is one of a modern range of polymer-framed handguns from the Czech firearms company. This high-capacity pistol is designed for law-enforcement and the military; it's the compact P-07's big brother. The P-09 also features the revolutionary Omega trigger mechanism.

Safety features include an ambidextrous, manually operated, frame-mounted safety catch (optionally a decocker) and an automatic firing pin block. All these are built around the proven Omega trigger system.

The slide features front serrations for easy cocking and is fitted with steel sights that feature contrasting, luminscent dots. Self-illuminating, Tritium night sights are an available option. Steel parts have an extremely durable surface finish.

The durable, fibreglass-reinforced polymer frame features an integral accessory rail for weapon-mounted lights, etc. The grip offers interchangeable backstraps that allows the shooter to alter the ergonomics to their preferred grip size - small, medium or large. The magazine release catch is reversible for left-handed shooters.

This model has a frame finished in the popular FDE (Flat Dark Earth) colour, and includes self-luminous Tritium night sights as standard.

name: CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black)
description:
The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow 9x19 Competition Pistol (Black) is a modern competition firearm with a traditional steel frame, chambered for 9mm Luger (9mm P, 9 x 19mm) calibre ammunition. This handgun holds 18 + 1 cartridges using the standard magazine; higher capacity magazines are available.

CZ designers teamed with some of the world's top competitive shooters to create the SP-01 range of full-sized, steel framed pistols from the solid foundation of the venerable CZ 75. While the Shadow dominates the IPSC Production Division, many security forces rely on the superb accuracy and reliability of other SP-01 variants.

The SP-01 range have great ergonomics designed into the grip, for a closer alignment for the bore axis to the hand. The magazine release catch is extended for easier actuation. The steel frame includes an integral MIL-STD-1913 tactical rail ahead of the trigger guard, for weapon mounted lights, etc. A bevelled magazine well assists with easy reloads.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights. All models feature an extended slide stop for easier operation.

The DA/SA trigger allows a typical "long, hard pull" for the first double-action shot, and a fantastic "short, crisp pull" for subsequent shots.

The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow has a 1.5mm red fibre-optic front sight, plain black Novak-style rear sight. This competition pistol features an ergonomic manual safety catch, but is without a firing pin safety for an improved trigger pull. It comes with checkered rubber grips.

CZ designers teamed with some of the world's top competitive shooters to create the SP-01 range of full-sized, steel framed pistols from the solid foundation of the venerable CZ 75. While the Shadow dominates the IPSC Production Division, many security forces rely on the superb accuracy and reliability of other SP-01 variants.

The SP-01 range have great ergonomics designed into the grip, for a closer alignment for the bore axis to the hand. The magazine release catch is extended for easier actuation. The steel frame includes an integral MIL-STD-1913 tactical rail ahead of the trigger guard, for weapon mounted lights, etc. A bevelled magazine well assists with easy reloads.

The top of the slide is enhanced with anti-reflective serrations for better shooting comfort, and is fitted with steel sights. All models feature an extended slide stop for easier operation.

The DA/SA trigger allows a typical "long, hard pull" for the first double-action shot, and a fantastic "short, crisp pull" for subsequent shots.

The CZ 75 SP-01 Shadow Orange has a 1.5mm red fibre-optic front sight, plain black Novak-style rear sight. This competition pistol features an ergonomic manual safety catch, but is without a firing pin safety for an improved trigger pull. This distinctive Orange model has bright orange anodised aluminium grip panels, as well as matching magazine base pads. The Orange offers enhanced accuracy through the hand fitted, polished barrel mated to a precisely fitted slide with minimum lateral tolerances. The improved trigger mechanism with re-designed hammer further enhances delivered precision.
